<br>
It seems though to me, a lot of people who aren't even necessarily Christian, believe in destiny.  I hear it all the time, &quot;This is your destiny&quot; and &quot;You were destined for this.&quot;  In Star Wars, Darth Vader said, &quot;Luke, it is your destiny.&quot;  Of course he believed it was Luke's destiny to join him on the dark side and obviously that wasn't his destiny.'<br>
<br>
I might not believe in destiny except I have no good answer for why I am able to believe and accept Jesus while others are not, even others within my own family.  And I often wonder, &quot;Why me?  Why am I able to 'get it' when others can't?&quot;<br>
<br>
So what do you think?  Is destiny a bad thing? <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">**********************************************<br>
